# 5️⃣ PERMISSION MODEL STRUCTURE

RBAC operates at three levels:

### Level 1 – System-Level Permissions

* Manage platform users
* View global analytics
* Override suspensions

### Level 2 – Organization-Level Permissions

* Create tenders
* Approve budgets
* Assign committee members

### Level 3 – Object-Level Permissions

* Access specific tender
* Edit specific bid
* View specific contract

---

# 6️⃣ PERMISSION MATRIX DESIGN

Example (Simplified):

| Action          | Buyer Admin | Evaluator | Supplier | Auditor |
| --------------- | ----------- | --------- | -------- | ------- |
| Create Tender   | ✅           | ❌         | ❌        | ❌       |
| Publish Tender  | ✅           | ❌         | ❌        | ❌       |
| Submit Bid      | ❌           | ❌         | ✅        | ❌       |
| Evaluate Bid    | ❌           | ✅         | ❌        | ❌       |
| Approve Award   | ✅           | ❌         | ❌        | ❌       |
| View Audit Logs | ❌           | ❌         | ❌        | ✅       |

